aboutSections.name: About
aboutSections.description: REEEMIX! Our chefs took the best parts of a burger and a classic banh mi and combined them to create...drumroll...THE WORLD’S GREATEST DINNER MASH-UP! Truly, there’s nothing we’d rather come home to at the end of the day than this bodacious beauty. Squishy toasted buns are filled with soy and garlic-spiked beef patties, shredded carrot, tangy pickled cucumber and onion, and a swoop of sriracha mayo. On the side, there’s a heap of carrot fries because, well, we just straight up love you. Yep, EP just hit you with anotha one.

aboutSections.name: The Exciting Part
aboutSections.description: When I think of a burger...I think of a delicious juicy patty, griddled to perfection, served with the most amazing sauce and fries that are bloody delicious. Now, for the exciting part. We add an asian twist, to an all American classic.

aboutSections.name: Pork and Beef
aboutSections.description: The ingredients in this recipe also play extraordinarily well with pork, so feel free to substitute the beef with pork. Just remember to use a perfect fat ratio for either one like 80-20 for the best eating experience!

steps.description: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve lime. Trim and peel carrots. Grate 1 carrot on the largest holes of a box grater until you have ¼ cup (½ cup for 4 servings). Cut remaining carrots into long thin sticks, like fries. (Ours were 3 inches long and ⅓ inch wide.) Halve, peel, and thinly slice ¼ of the onion (½ the onion for 4; save the rest for another use). Trim and halve cucumber lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons.
Toss carrot sticks on a baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. Roast, tossing halfway through, until golden brown and tender, 15-20 minutes.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, toss together sliced onion, cucumber, juice from whole lime (juice from both limes for 4 servings),  1 tsp sugar (2 tsp for 4), salt, and pepper. Set aside to quick-pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Peel and finely chop garlic. In a medium bowl, combine beef, soy sauce, half the garlic, ½ tsp sugar (1 tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper. Form into two ½-inch-thick patties (four patties for 4). Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, 3-5 minutes per side.
While patties cook, in a second small bowl, combine mayonnaise, a pinch of remaining garlic, and as much sriracha as you’d like. Season with salt and pepper.

Halve buns; toast directly on oven rack until golden brown, 3-5 minutes. Divide toasted buns between plates. Spread cut sides with sriracha mayo, then fill with patties, a bit of grated carrot, and some pickled veggies. Serve with carrot fries on the side and ketchup for dipping if desired.
